title: My Raspberry Pi Collector's Edition app for android
description: The Raspberry Pi Song is a love song dedicated to the infamous single-board computer known as Rasberry Pi. In this record, the Raspberry Pi adventurer, cryptocurrency enthusiast, entertainer, and hip-hop artist/lyricist Saint Ignatius of Cyberspace parallels love to computing by drawing on his previous experience of dysfunctional dating relationships, emphasizing that he would rather choose the single board computer as a partner. In this Collector's Edition listeners will also have the ability to stream and download the single "My Raspberry Pi (A Love Song)," and set the song as a ringtone. In addition, the application includes the lyrics which can be read along during song play, a downloadable Collector's Edition Graffiti Art on a Raspberry Pi background Wallpaper, a Raspberry Pi Hacks video feed, social media, and more. The Raspberry Pi Song will also be featured in the up and coming album "Binary Gospell EP" by Saint Ignatius of Cyberspace, which is a Raspberry Pi project currently in the works, and will be recorded on a Raspberry Pi 3 B+, and is expected to be completed sometime by end of 2018. http://www.saintignati.us http://www.apptyze.com Music used: Hello Mr. Princeton by Otis McDonald Licensed under Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 BTC: 1Pu1ymV3gb622E3GcTRPt2YZmomMzKyHES ETH: 0x700f358098df656c57abecb2c61f664efdd1f97d LTC: LTbXoG7UXaLhJCA1dbyoCgQvc2mSR67eTk Binary Gospell EP (The Album): The Binary Gospell EP is a Raspberry Pi project currently in the works and is a hip-hop studio album by Saint Ignatius of Cyberspace, expected to be fully completed and launched by end of 2018. The album will focus on delivering a sound that resonates with the uplifting soulful and funky '90's era sample based conscious hip-hop with an overtone of live instrument play (ex. The Roots), while the lyrical content and rhymes will be driven by principles of lyricism which will cover a wide range of topics belonging to the lifestyle of a typical millennial geek (ex. Saint Ignatius of Cyberspace)
